HEADWORD: Pug nose
<hw>Pug" nose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A short, thick nose; a
snubnose.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pug"-nosed`</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pug-nose eel</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
deep-water marine eel (<spn>Simenchelys parasiticus</spn>) which
sometimes burrows into the flesh of the halibut.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

